#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
swg-panel-server — the panel broker.

Serves the app and brokers peer operations to nodes over a per-node transport
(local subprocess / ssh forced-command / async queue). A peer is one identity
that can be deployed to several nodes for redundancy: the panel picks an address
free on every selected node, pushes the same pubkey + IP + PSK to each, and
records the node set. Reads (describe / next-ip) for local & ssh hit the agent
live; for queue nodes they come from the node's pushed snapshot.

The browser generates the private key and PSK. The PSK transits once to
configure each node and is never written to the roster. Per-node client configs
are stored only when store_configs is on (then they contain the private key).

Config: /etc/swg-panel/fleet.json   (see fleet.example.json)
Standalone: set SWG_PANEL_TLS_CERT/KEY + SWG_PANEL_AUTH and bind 0.0.0.0 to serve
HTTPS + Basic-Auth + /wgstats directly. Or bind 127.0.0.1 behind your own nginx.
"""

