# small box the cost scales with tab count. Memoize the SERIALIZED bytes for a short TTL: within one window
# only the FIRST request builds; the rest just re-send the cached bytes (skipping both the assembly and the
# json.dumps). A successful mutation invalidates it (see do_POST) so user actions still reflect immediately;
# node-sync freshness (counters/snapshots) simply lags by at most the TTL, which keeps caching effective no
# matter how many nodes or tabs there are.
